Pimco Hires Ex-Citadel Securities Research Chief Mattu to Head Analytics

-- B y   S r e e   V i d y a   B h a k t a v a t s a l a m
-- 
2011-02-22T17:43:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/pimco-hires-ex-citadel-hedge-fund-research-head-mattu-to-lead-analytics.html
Pacific Investment Management Co.
hired Ravi Mattu, a former head of research and strategy for
Citadel Securities, as managing director in charge of analytics.  Mattu will report to Chief Executive Officer Mohamed El-
Erian,  Newport Beach , California-based Pimco said today in a
statement. He will start at Pimco on March 2.  Mattu left Citadel Securities, the investment-banking unit
of Chicago hedge fund Citadel LLC, in July, following a series
of departures among senior management at the unit. In his new
role at Pimco, he will help clients analyze their portfolios.  “Ravi’s mandate is to expand our state-of-the-art
analytics solutions for Pimco’s clients,” El-Erian and  Bill
Gross , Pimco’s co-chief investment officers, wrote in a letter
to employees today. “Having a world-class integrated analytics
framework has been key to Pimco’s success, and remains so,”
they wrote.  Pimco, which manages $1.24 trillion, runs the world’s
biggest mutual fund.  To contact the reporter on this story:
